{
  "nbformat": 4,
  "nbformat_minor": 5,
  "metadata": {
    "kernelspec": {
      "name": "maxima",
      "display_name": "Maxima",
      "language": "maxima"
    },
    "aximar": {}
  },
  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "# Symbolic vs Numeric Integration\n\nThis notebook demonstrates Maxima's **symbolic-numeric bridge** by comparing\nexact symbolic integration (`integrate()`) with numeric trapezoidal\napproximation (`np_trapz()`). We explore convergence, special functions,\noscillatory integrands, and the Fundamental Theorem of Calculus.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "load(\"numerics\")$\nload(\"ax-plots\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 10,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Exact Symbolic Integration\n\nMaxima computes closed-form antiderivatives using its powerful symbolic\nengine. No discretisation, no approximation -- just exact algebra.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Polynomial: integral of x^2 from 0 to 1 */\nexact1 : integrate(x^2, x, 0, 1);\n\n/* Trigonometric: integral of sin(x) from 0 to pi */\nexact2 : integrate(sin(x), x, 0, %pi);",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 11,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "1/3"
          ]
        },
        {
          "data": {
            "text/latex": [
              "2"
            ]
          },
          "execution_count": 11,
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "execute_result"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Numeric Approximation with np_trapz\n\nThe trapezoidal rule approximates the integral by summing trapezoids\nunder a sampled curve. With `np_linspace` we create a grid, evaluate\nthe function, and feed both arrays to `np_trapz`.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Approximate integral of x^2 on [0,1] with 10 points */\nxs : np_linspace(0, 1, 10)$\nys : np_pow(xs, 2)$\nnumeric1 : np_trapz(ys, xs);\nprint(\"Exact:\", 1/3, \"  Numeric:\", numeric1)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 12,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "0.3353909465020576\nExact: 1/3   Numeric: 0.3353909465020576"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Approximate integral of sin(x) on [0, pi] with 50 points */\nxs2 : np_linspace(0, float(%pi), 50)$\nys2 : np_map(sin, xs2)$\nnumeric2 : np_trapz(ys2, xs2);\nprint(\"Exact: 2\", \"  Numeric:\", numeric2)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 13,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "1.9993148493240624\nExact: 2   Numeric: 1.9993148493240624"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Convergence Study\n\nHow does the trapezoidal error decrease as we add more sample points?\nFor $f(x) = e^{-x^2}$ on $[0, 3]$, the trapezoidal rule has error\n$O(h^2) = O(1/n^2)$. We verify this by computing the error at several\nresolutions and plotting on a log-log scale.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Exact value via symbolic integration + float conversion */\nexact_gauss : float(integrate(exp(-t^2), t, 0, 3))$\nprint(\"Exact integral of exp(-x^2) on [0,3]:\", exact_gauss)$\n\n/* Sweep over increasing number of points */\nns : [10, 20, 50, 100, 200, 500, 1000]$\nerrors : makelist(\n  block([xg, yg, approx],\n    xg : np_linspace(0, 3, ns[i]),\n    yg : np_map(lambda([z], exp(-z^2)), xg),\n    approx : np_trapz(yg, xg),\n    abs(approx - exact_gauss)),\n  i, 1, length(ns))$\nprint(\"Errors:\", errors)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 14,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Exact integral of exp(-x^2) on [0,3]: 0.8862073482595211\nErrors:\n       [6.495944890105854e-6,1.5194130239537529e-6,2.308643267667776e-7,\n        5.663598212635179e-8,1.402189420129929e-8,2.2302486524239384e-9,\n        5.564541050162575e-10]"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Log-log convergence plot */\nlog_ns : map(lambda([n], float(log(n))), ns)$\nlog_errs : map(lambda([e], float(log(e))), errors)$\nax_draw2d(\n  color=blue, name=\"measured error\",\n  points(log_ns, log_errs),\n  color=red, dash=\"dash\", name=\"O(1/n^2) reference\",\n  lines([float(log(10)), float(log(1000))],\n        [log_errs[1], log_errs[1] - 2*(float(log(1000))-float(log(10)))]),\n  title=\"Trapezoidal Rule Convergence\",\n  xlabel=\"log(n)\", ylabel=\"log(error)\", grid=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 15,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "data": {
            "application/x-maxima-plotly": [
              "{\"data\":[{\"x\":[2.302585092994046,2.995732273553991,3.912023005428146,4.605170185988092,5.298317366548036,6.214608098422191,6.907755278982137],\"y\":[-11.944332438806855,-13.397186466139805,-15.281435628984404,-16.686621327111848,-18.08264585738342,-19.921152754361298,-21.309436419384276],\"type\":\"scatter\",\"mode\":\"markers\",\"marker\":{\"color\":\"blue\",\"size\":6},\"name\":\"measured error\"},{\"x\":[2.302585092994046,6.907755278982137],\"y\":[-11.944332438806855,-21.154672810783037],\"type\":\"scatter\",\"mode\":\"lines\",\"line\":{\"color\":\"red\",\"width\":2,\"dash\":\"dash\"},\"name\":\"O(1/n^2) reference\"}],\"layout\":{\"title\":{\"text\":\"Trapezoidal Rule Convergence\"},\"width\":700,\"height\":450,\"plot_bgcolor\":\"white\",\"paper_bgcolor\":\"white\",\"xaxis\":{\"title\":{\"text\":\"log(n)\"},\"showgrid\":true,\"gridcolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linecolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linewidth\":1,\"zerolinecolor\":\"black\",\"zerolinewidth\":1},\"yaxis\":{\"title\":{\"text\":\"log(error)\"},\"showgrid\":true,\"gridcolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linecolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linewidth\":1,\"zerolinecolor\":\"black\",\"zerolinewidth\":1}}}"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "display_data"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Integrating Special Functions\n\nMaxima can evaluate improper integrals that would be difficult or\nimpossible to compute numerically. For example, $\\int_0^\\infty \\frac{1}{1+x^4}\\,dx$\nhas an exact closed form involving radicals.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Exact symbolic result for an improper integral */\nexact_special : integrate(1/(1+x^4), x, 0, inf);\nprint(\"Exact:\", float(exact_special))$\n\n/* Numeric approximation on [0, 100] (truncated tail) */\nxs3 : np_linspace(0, 100, 5000)$\nys3 : np_map(lambda([z], 1/(1+z^4)), xs3)$\nprint(\"np_trapz on [0,100]:\", np_trapz(ys3, xs3))$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 16,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "%pi/2^(3/2)\nExact: 1.1107207345395913\nnp_trapz on [0,100]: 1.110720401206242"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Oscillatory Integrals\n\nWhen the integrand oscillates rapidly, numeric methods need many sample\npoints to avoid aliasing. Symbolic integration handles this effortlessly.\nWe compare `np_trapz` at two resolutions for $g(x) = \\sin(10x)\\,e^{-x}$.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Exact symbolic integral of sin(10*x)*exp(-x) on [0, 2*pi] */\nexact_osc : float(integrate(sin(10*t)*exp(-t), t, 0, 2*%pi));\n\n/* Numeric with n=100 (under-resolved) vs n=1000 */\nxo1 : np_linspace(0, float(2*%pi), 100)$\nyo1 : np_map(lambda([z], sin(10*z)*exp(-z)), xo1)$\nxo2 : np_linspace(0, float(2*%pi), 1000)$\nyo2 : np_map(lambda([z], sin(10*z)*exp(-z)), xo2)$\nprint(\"n=100:\", np_trapz(yo1, xo1),\n      \"  n=1000:\", np_trapz(yo2, xo2))$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 17,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "0.09882500567012793\nn=100: 0.09545259472279734   n=1000: 0.09879210054768726"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Plot the oscillatory integrand with shaded area */\nxp : np_linspace(0, float(2*%pi), 500)$\nyp : np_map(lambda([z], sin(10*z)*exp(-z)), xp)$\nax_draw2d(\n  color=blue, fill=\"tozeroy\", opacity=0.3,\n  name=\"sin(10x) exp(-x)\",\n  lines(xp, yp),\n  title=\"Oscillatory Integrand\",\n  xlabel=\"x\", ylabel=\"g(x)\", grid=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 18,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "data": {
