          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "display_data"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## The Fundamental Theorem of Calculus\n\nThe FTC says $\\frac{d}{dx}\\int_0^x f(t)\\,dt = f(x)$.\nWe verify this two ways: first **symbolically** — Maxima integrates\n$1/(1+t^2)$ to get $\\arctan(x)$, then differentiates to recover the\nintegrand — and then **numerically** — we accumulate `np_trapz` values\nat many points, take finite differences, and compare against $f(x)$.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Symbolic FTC: integrate then differentiate */\nassume(x > 0)$\nF_sym : integrate(1/(1+t^2), t, 0, x);\nresult : diff(F_sym, x);\nis(ratsimp(result - 1/(1+x^2)) = 0);",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 19,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "atan(x)\n1/(x^2+1)"
          ]
        },
        {
          "data": {
            "text/latex": [
              "\\mathbf{true}"
            ]
          },
          "execution_count": 19,
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "execute_result"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Numeric FTC: accumulate trapezoid sums F(x_k), then\n   approximate F'(x_k) with finite differences */\nnpts : 500$\nxf : np_linspace(0, 5, npts)$\nyf : np_map(lambda([z], 1/(1+z^2)), xf)$\ny_list : np_to_list(yf)$\n\n/* F(x_k) = cumulative trapezoid sum from 0 to x_k */\ndx : 5.0 / (npts - 1)$\nF_vals : [0.0]$\nfor k : 2 thru npts do\n  F_vals : endcons(last(F_vals) + dx * (y_list[k-1] + y_list[k]) / 2, F_vals)$\n\n/* Numeric derivative: dF/dx via central differences */\ndFdx : makelist(\n  if i = 1 then (F_vals[2] - F_vals[1]) / dx\n  elseif i = npts then (F_vals[i] - F_vals[i-1]) / dx\n  else (F_vals[i+1] - F_vals[i-1]) / (2*dx),\n  i, 1, npts)$\n\n/* Compare against exact f(x) = 1/(1+x^2) */\nx_list : np_to_list(xf)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 20,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "ax_draw2d(\n  color=\"steelblue\", line_width=2, name=\"f(x) = 1/(1+x^2)\",\n  lines(x_list, y_list),\n  color=\"red\", dash=\"dash\", line_width=2, name=\"d/dx [trapz sum]\",\n  lines(x_list, dFdx),\n  title=\"FTC Verification: Numeric Derivative of Numeric Integral\",\n  xlabel=\"x\", ylabel=\"f(x)\", grid=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 21,
