    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Summary\n\n- **Symbolic integration** (`integrate`) gives exact, closed-form answers\n  for a wide class of integrands, including improper integrals and special\n  functions.\n- **Numeric integration** (`np_trapz`) is useful when symbolic methods fail,\n  when data is empirical or tabulated, or when a quick numerical check is\n  needed. Its accuracy improves as $O(1/n^2)$.\n- Maxima's symbolic-numeric bridge lets you derive formulas symbolically,\n  then validate or visualise them numerically -- the best of both worlds.",
      "metadata": {}
    }
  ]
}